body_html:
@girving @josh11b It seems //tensorflow/core/ops/compat:backwards_compatibility_test does not work properly. I added this for op name: "Sin" to make the test fail:

--- a/tensorflow/core/ops/compat/ops_history.v0.pbtxt
+++ b/tensorflow/core/ops/compat/ops_history.v0.pbtxt
@@ -16883,7 +16883,8 @@ op {
         type: DT_DOUBLE
         type: DT_INT32
         type: DT_COMPLEX64
-        type: DT_INT64
+        type: DT_STRING
+        type: DT_SHOULD_FAIL
       }
     }
   }

I think the test should fail, but it passes:

INFO: Elapsed time: 3.883s, Critical Path: 0.63s
//tensorflow/core/ops/compat:backwards_compatibility_test                PASSED in 0.6s

Did I miss something?

``` diff
--- a/tensorflow/core/ops/compat/ops_history.v0.pbtxt
+++ b/tensorflow/core/ops/compat/ops_history.v0.pbtxt
@@ -16883,7 +16883,8 @@ op {
         type: DT_DOUBLE
         type: DT_INT32
         type: DT_COMPLEX64
-        type: DT_INT64
+        type: DT_STRING
+        type: DT_SHOULD_FAIL
       }
     }
   }
```

I think the test should fail, but it passes:

Did I miss something?
